        <div class="py-4">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Galaxy Data Analysis -
                    <a target="_blank" href="http://www.princeton.edu/genomics">Lewis-Sigler Institute for Integrative Genomics</a>
                </h2>
                {% if env == 'development' %}
                    <div class="errormessagelarge" id="development-notice">
                        <h1>DEVELOPMENT SERVER</h1>
                        <h3>ALL DATA IS SUBJECT TO REMOVAL WITHOUT NOTICE!</h3>
                    </div>
                {% endif %}
            </div>
            <br>
            <div class="donemessagelarge container">
                <h3>Learn Galaxy</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Take an interactive tour:
                        <a target="_parent" href="../tours/core.galaxy_ui" class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm">Galaxy UI</a>
                        <a target="_parent" href="../tours/core.history" class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm">History</a>
                        <a target="_parent" href="../tours/core.scratchbook" class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm">Scratchbook</a>
                    </li>
                    <li><a target="_blank" href="https://galaxyproject.org/learn/">Learn Galaxy</a> -
                        There are many approaches to learning how to use Galaxy. The most popular is
                        probably to just dive in and use it. Galaxy is simple enough to use that you can
                        do many analyses just by exploring the interface. However, you may miss much of
                        the power this way.</li>
                    <li><a target="_blank" href="https://galaxyproject.github.io/training-material/">Galaxy Training</a> -
                        Collection of tutorials developed and maintained by the worldwide Galaxy community.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Princeton Community</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Join the
                        <a target="_blank" href="https://sites.google.com/site/princetonhtseq/">Princeton HTSEQ Users Group</a>,
                        discuss, present, and learn from other users in the Princeton research community</li>
                    <li>Get expert advice from the
                        <a target="_blank" href="http://www.princeton.edu/genomics/sequencing/">Lewis-Sigler Sequencing Core Facility</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <br>
            <div class="infomessagelarge container" id="updates">
                <h3>What's New</h3>
                <h4>
                    <a
                        target="_blank"
                        href="https://docs.galaxyproject.org/en/master/releases/20.05_announce_user.html">Galaxy Release 20.05</a>
                </h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>New Interactive Tools</strong>
                        <p>Through the combined efforts of many UseGalaxy.eu admins and developers, as well as
                        the European Galaxy community we have converted a significant number of interactive
                        environments into the new interactive tool specification. Thanks to
                        <a href="https://github.com/bgruening">@bgruening</a>,
                        <a href="https://github.com/hexylena">@hexylena</a>,
                        <a href="https://github.com/jenzopr">@jenzopr</a>,
                        <a href="https://github.com/yvanlebras">@yvanlebras</a>,
                        <a href="https://github.com/annefou">@annefou</a>,
                        <a href="https://github.com/abretaud">@abretaud</a>,
                        <a href="https://github.com/joachimwolff">@joachimwolff</a>, and
                        <a href="https://github.com/astrovsky01">@astrovsky01</a>. You can try
                        them all on <a href="https://live.usegalaxy.eu/">live.usegalaxy.eu</a></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Rule Based Uploader: Scrolling!</strong>
                        <p>Many power users have fallen in love with Galaxyâ€™s Rule Builder, allowing you to upload
                        tables of data, and easily tag datasets and build collections on upload. However with too
                        many columns the table did not scroll well for users, but no longer! This has been fixed
                        by one of the Galaxy team members, <a href="https://github.com/assuntad23">@assuntad23</a>.
                        If you want to learn more about using the rule builder please see the 
                        <a href="https://training.galaxyproject.org/training-material/topics/galaxy-data-manipulation/tutorials/upload-rules/tutorial.html">in-depth tutorial</a>
                        from the developer, <a href="https://github.com/jmchilton">@jmchilton</a>.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="errormessagelarge container" id="diskspace-notice">
                <h3>Disk Space is Limited</h3>
                <h4>Please delete datasets you no longer need to make room for others</h4>
                <p>By viewing your list of saved histories, you can see how much space each is
                    taking up. Please delete any histories that you no longer need. Your cooperation
                    is appreciated.
                </p>
                <h4>Data stored for more than 30 days may be deleted without notice.</h4>
            </div>

            <div class="warningmessagelarge container" id="maintenance-notice">
                <h3>Scheduled Maintenance</h3>
                <p>The Galaxy system will undergo scheduled maintenance on the first Monday of
                    each month from 9am-12pm.</p>
            </div>
        </div>


